    <stitle>No Idle APU/HVAC System - System Identification - Battery Charger</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Battery Charger</title>
        <para>The battery charger is a 12VDC/50 Amp output unit. The input voltage is 120VAC (fed from the power
            distribution box), which allows the unit to operate while the APU is running or while the system is
            connected to shore power.
        </para>
        <para>Battery charger features include:</para>
        <randlist type="bullet">
            <item>
                <para>Over-current shutdown</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Reverse polarity protection</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Ignition protection</para>
            </item>
        </randlist>
        <para>
            <emph type="bold">*The battery charger is integrated into the HVAC module.</emph>
        </para>
    </svcproc>
